 Police in Queenstown have appealed to the public for assistance in locating a missing teen from the area According to police spokesperson, Namhla Mdleleni, it is alleged that the 19-year-old learner, Siphesande Sibulele Nogela, who is a student at the Royal Academy, was last seen at school on Thursday. “After school, he did not return to his home in Kingspark,” she said. “He was wearing his school uniform, a dark blue blazer with white stripes, white shirt, and grey trousers.” Anyone, who can assist with the information can please contact Detective Sgt Funeka Mvandaba at 045 8086023 /0860010111.   